<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 11:18PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow along portions of I-15 overnight...
Areas of light snow will affects locations along I-15 from Craig
to Elk Park overnight tonight. Visibility will fall to around one
mile at times, with new snow accumulations up to an inch.
Some roadways could become snow covered and slippery. Those
traveling along the I-15 corridor area from north of Butte to
Craig should be alert for quickly changing road conditions.</description>
